    <note>Bi(1) Shian [8107] His ancestors were Dongping jun Bi(1). At the end of Tang and beginning of the Five Dynasties, this lineage branch of the clan moved to Daizhou. Shian moved to Zhengzhou, Guancheng xian and the Daizhou Bi(1) lineage became Zhengzhou Bi(1). Qingchang's [7315] father, Zhongyan's [1416] and Zhongyou's [1417] great grandfather, Liangshi's [1418] fifth generation ancestor. Grandfather-in-law of Song(2) Shou [1575], and of Liu(2) Xigu's [8091] grandson. Song(2) Minqiu's [1571] great grandfather-in-law. His second son's father-in-law was Kou(1) Zhun [898] (twice: sororate). Bi Zhongyou, WJ, 14.4b, 16.1a-15a; Du Dagui, 'xia,' 4.1a; Yang Yi, WJ, 11.1a-9a; Liu Zhi, WJ, 11.1a-9b. CBD, 3, 2711-2.</note>
